      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nPeng, it isn't permitted to land patches without a proper ticket number. An invalid ticket like LU-000 is only useful if the patch is for testing purposes and is never meant to land.\n\nIn case of a bug like this, it is good to have a proper Jira ticket, since it needs to be tracked against a release, and potentially landed on multiple branches (depending on when it was introduced).",
